Interface MviPresenter<V extends MvpView,VS>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - The type of the View this presenter responds to
    VS - The type of the ViewState (Model)
    All Superinterfaces:
    MvpPresenter<V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:

    public interface MviPresenter<V extends MvpView,VS>
extends MvpPresenter<V>
    This type of presenter is responsible to interact with the viewState in a Model-View-Intent way. A MviPresenter is the bridge that is responsible to setup the reactive flow between viewState and model
